"lazy"/></a><!--]--></div></div><!--]--></div></div><!----><!----> <main class="p-grid-container" id="main"><article class="p-grid-text-container"><!--[--><header><div class="p-opener p-opener--full p-opener--left p-opener--full-hed-over-art svelte-1jvv67g"><div class="p-opener__art-wrapper svelte-1jvv67g"><figure class="svelte-1jvv67g"><img class="p-opener__art svelte-1jvv67g" alt="A collage overlays a black-and-white photo of a wooden sign reading “Measles testing” in a scene with a Texas flag in the background. Illustrations of genetic sequences and branching diagrams surround the sign, with red banners highlighting various DNA configurations that are labeled with locations and dates from Texas and Utah." src="https://www.propublica.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/20260605-measles-testing-us-5x2-1.jpg" srcset="
